{
  "format_version": "1.2",
  "terraform_version": "1.9.0",
  "_comment": "A clean, HARDENED Hetzner/Talos plan mirroring the shipped template's resource SHAPE (infra/templates/project/hetzner: servers.tf firewall_ids on every hcloud_server, network.tf hcloud_firewall with rule blocks + private hcloud_network). Difference from the shipped default: the management rules (6443/50000/50001) here source from the PRIVATE node CIDR rather than 0.0.0.0/0, so HCLOUD-NET-001 has nothing world-open to flag -> a genuine PASS. This is the mutation-gate baseline (mutate_test.go): strip a server's firewall_ids -> HCLOUD-FW-001 fails; add a world-open :22 rule -> HCLOUD-NET-001 fails.",
  "resource_changes": [
    {
